\section{Simulators and Examples}
\subsection{Logisim Simulator}
In the following  \htmladdnormallink{link}{http://ozark.hendrix.edu/~burch/logisim/} you will find a graphical tool for designing and simulating combinational and synchronous circuits.

\noindent
Some examples of implementation using Logisim (download the file and open it using Logisim):
\begin{enumerate}
  \item \htmladdnormallink{The 3-bit carry function}{./Code/3bitcarry.circ}. This function appears on Chapter~1,~15, etc.
  \item \htmladdnormallink{The AND(4) function}{./Code/AND4.circ}. This function appears on Chapter~12,~13, etc.
  \item \htmladdnormallink{The DECODER(3) function}{./Code/DEC_1.circ}. This function appears on Chapter~13, etc.
  \end{enumerate}
  
\subsection{DLX simulator}
In the following  \htmladdnormallink{link}{./resa8.zip} you will find a simulator of
The Simplified DLX that appears on Chapters~21 and~22.

\noindent
This simulator can be used to write programs in the DLX's machine language, and to execute and debug these programs.

\noindent
For example: \htmladdnormallink{Example 21.9}{./Code/example219.s}.
